data.title: NASCAR Chicago Street Race: Starting lineup, TV schedule for Sunday's race
data.meta_description: The 2024 NASCAR Cup Series season continues with the Grant Park 165 at the Chicago Street Race on Sunday. See the starting lineup here.
data.text:
Kyle Larson is on the pole for the second year of the NASCAR Chicago Street Race's Grant Park 165. Larson dueled street race pro Shane van Gisbergen during Saturday's Xfinity race, which was won by van Gisbergen. Larson was third, behind Ty Gibbs.

Last year's inaugural Chicago Street Race was won by van Gisbergen.

Here's the full starting lineup for Sunday's Grant Park 165.

HERE TO STAY: Why the NASCAR Cup Series left Nashville and why it could be here to stay

NASHVILLE ANALYSIS: Nashville NASCAR race winners, losers: Joey Logano gets needed win, Kyle Busch bad luck continues

NASCAR Chicago Street Race TV schedule, start time for Grant Park 165

Green Flag Time: Approx. 3:30 p.m. CT on Sunday, July, 7

Track: Chicago Street course (2.2-mile street course with 12 turns) in Chicago

Length: 75 laps, 165 miles

Stages: 20 laps, 25 laps, 30 laps

TV coverage: NBC

Radio: PRN (102.5 FM in Nashville)

Streaming: FUBO (free trial available); NBC Sports app (subscription required); GoPRN.com and SiriusXM on Channel 90 for audio (subscription required)
